<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-07-0333 </DOCNO><TEXT>Social and institutional linkages and political cultures influence assumptionsabout nature and society: assumptions that in turn underlie the cognitiveand normative framework which produces the variety of competing models.In this perspective, models are systematic codifications of cognitiveand social structures, developed by actors to promote their interestsand/or world views. Understanding the modelling process therefore alsoimplies understanding the structure and process of political systemsthat surround it. By contrasting the simplistic representations of therelationship between model and society found in, for example, the social-engineeringperspectives with the more complex social-systems perspective proposed,attention is drawn to some key elements of the analysis presented.</TEXT></DOC>